# UI Components Guide

This application uses a Studio Ghibli-inspired design language with light, ethereal UI components.

## Key UI Components

### Image Upload and Transformation
- [components/UploadPanel.tsx](mdc:components/UploadPanel.tsx) - Handles the upload area UI
- [components/ImageResult.tsx](mdc:components/ImageResult.tsx) - Displays transformation results
- [components/ImageCarousel.tsx](mdc:components/ImageCarousel.tsx) - Shows before/after image comparisons

### Animation Components
- [components/GhibliFloatingElements.tsx](mdc:components/GhibliFloatingElements.tsx) - Animated floating elements in Ghibli style
- [components/GhibliBackground.tsx](mdc:components/GhibliBackground.tsx) - Animated background in Ghibli style
- [components/MouseFollower.tsx](mdc:components/MouseFollower.tsx) - Animated element that follows the mouse cursor

### Layout Components
- [components/Header.tsx](mdc:components/Header.tsx) - Site header with navigation
- [components/Footer.tsx](mdc:components/Footer.tsx) - Site footer
- [components/LanguageSwitcher.tsx](mdc:components/LanguageSwitcher.tsx) - Language switching component

## Design Pattern Notes

1. The site uses a light, airy color scheme inspired by Studio Ghibli films
2. UI components feature rounded corners and soft shadows
3. Animations are subtle and whimsical to match the Ghibli aesthetic
4. Backgrounds use gradient overlays for a dreamy effect
5. Component organization follows a clear hierarchy with distinct sections for upload, examples, and results
